 <refentry id="function.image-type-to-mime-type">
  <refnamediv>
   <refname>image_type_to_mime_type</refname>
   <refpurpose>Lit le Mime-Type d'un type d'image</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsect1>
   <title>Description</title>
    <methodsynopsis>
     <type>string </type><methodname>image_type_to_mime_type</methodname>
     <methodparam><type>int</type><parameter>imagetype</parameter></methodparam>
    </methodsynopsis>
   <para>
    <function>image_type_to_mime_type</function> d&eacute;termine le type
    Mime (Mime-Type), &agrave; utiliser dans l'en-t&ecirc;te HTTP <literal>Content-type</literal>.
    <parameter>imagetype</parameter> est une constante, repr&eacute;sentant un
    type d'image, et retourn&eacute;e par 
    <function>getimagesize</function>, 
    <function>exif_read_data</function>, <function>exif_thumbnail</function> ou
    <function>exif_imagetype</function>.
    <example>
     <title>image_type_to_mime_type (file)</title>
     <programlisting role="php">
<![CDATA[
<?php
header ("Content-type: ".image_type_to_mime_type (IMAGETYPE_PNG));
?>
]]>
     </programlisting>
    </example>
   </para>
   <para>
    <note>
     <simpara>
      Cette fonction ne requiert par la librairie GD.
     </simpara>
     <simpara>
      Voir ausi
      <function>getimagesize</function>, 
      <function>exif_imagetype</function>, 
      <function>exif_read_data</function> et
      <function>exif_thumbnail</function>.
     </simpara>
    </note>
   </para>
  </refsect1>
 </refentry>

